                    	<note xml:id="n_remarks" type="remarks">
                    	    
                                    
<p>Postcard (2½ cents). Postmarks: ‘NUENEN 8-12 V / 9 APR 85’ and ‘EINDHOVEN 12-1 N / 9 APR 85’. The address reads: ‘WelEd Heer A. Kerssemakers Simonis/ <hi rend="italics">Eindhoven</hi>’ (Kerssemakers was married to Josephina Dymphina Simonis).</p>
                                    
                                
                    	</note>
                    
                </listAnnotation>
                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="ogtnotes">
                    
                        <note n="1" xml:id="ogt_1">
                            
<p>Preparations for <hi rend="italics">The potato eaters</hi> <ref target="let490.xml">(490)</ref></p>
                        </note>
                        
                            

                        
                    
                </listAnnotation>
                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="notes">
                    
                        <note n="1" xml:id="note-t-1">
                            
    
<p>One of these studies is still extant: <hi rend="italics">Man and a woman planting potatoes</hi> (<rs type="artwork" ref="artwork.xml#ill_2503">F 129a / JH 727</rs>), after which the letter sketch of the same name was made (<rs type="artwork" ref="artwork.xml#_144">F - / JH 728</rs>). The composition of the other one is now known only from <hi rend="italics">Two women working in the fields </hi>(<rs type="artwork" ref="artwork.xml#_145">F 1228 / JH 730</rs>), the sketch enclosed with <ref target="let492.xml">letter 492</ref>.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                            

                        
                    
